<plot>Witty, intellectual and a little dark-humored with top-notch production value, 'How to Be a Director' is a sarcastic and fun-filled comedy about the entertainment business as demonstrated by a ten-step 'spoof-o-mercial.' Daniel F. Scherl and Jolene Kay take you on a fast-paced, hilarious ride through the ups and downs of what it's really like in the crazy world of acting and directing in Hollywood. Do you have what it takes... to be a DIRECTOR!?!</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?248462</url></doc>
